  { q: "Who owns Dexter Commercial Laundry?", a: "Dexter Laundry Inc. is 100% employee-owned through an ESOP (Employee Stock Ownership Plan) — company-owned by its employees since 2004. Headquartered in Fairfield, Iowa, where Dexter has been manufacturing commercial laundry equipment since 1894. The ESOP structure puts Dexter in the same employee-ownership category as Alliance Laundry Systems (Speed Queen parent, ESOP since 2018), but Dexter reached ESOP status 14 years earlier. Dexter is NOT part of Alliance, NOT Ali Group, NOT ITW, NOT Welbilt — it's an independent employee-owned manufacturer. That matters operationally for parts supply: Dexter's parts distribution runs through its own Fairfield-direct and authorized distributor network, not through a conglomerate parts warehouse. LA laundromat operators specifying Dexter versus Speed Queen usually do so on specific operational preferences — Dexter has a loyal segment of the laundromat market and competes head-to-head at the mid-to-upper spec tier." },
  { q: "Which Dexter models do you see most in LA?", a: "Dexter's O-Series + T-Series lineup covers most of the LA install base. O-Series OPL front-loads (O-Series 20, 30, 40, 55, 60, 80 lb capacities) ship into hotel and institutional OPL; T-Series (T-350, T-450, T-600, T-750, T-900, T-1200 hardmount + soft-mount variants) is the laundromat-focused line with coin, card, and OPL programmable variants. T-80 stack washer/dryer is the constrained-space unit for apartment laundry rooms and smaller OPL installs. Express washers (Express 20, 30, 40, 60, 80 lb) focus on high-speed cycles for vended laundromat revenue-per-hour optimization. Dryers: T30, T50, T80 single-pocket plus DL2X30 stack dryer. Our LA Dexter service covers all of these plus legacy Dexter units still running at long-established laundromats." },
  { q: "Dexter vs Speed Queen — how do they compare for LA laundromat spec?", a: "Both employee-owned, both mid-to-upper spec tier, different engineering philosophies. Speed Queen (Alliance, 2018 ESOP, Ripon WI, 1908 heritage) runs the larger LA install base and dominates default new-laundromat specifications. Dexter (independent ESOP since 2004, Fairfield IA, 1894 heritage) has a smaller but fiercely loyal segment — laundromat operators who've run Dexter for decades often stay on Dexter through refits. Parts supply is comparable in LA: both have authorized distributor networks covering the region with 1-3 day lead on common parts, stock parts available on service trucks. The practical difference for an operator running one brand: parts commonality within your own fleet matters more than brand-to-brand comparison. Our service covers both without brand preference — call us with the model number and we route the parts through the correct distributor." },
  { q: "Dexter T-Series card-reader integration — do you service the coin+card retrofit?", a: "Yes. Dexter T-Series washers and dryers ship in coin-op, card-ready, and OPL-programmable variants. Retrofit from pure coin to card + app payment systems is a common project at LA laundromats updating to ESD or Card Concepts card systems, or to modern app-integrated payment platforms like CleanCloud or Cents. We handle the mechanical side of the retrofit — wiring the card reader harness to the Dexter control board, programming the control panel for card-mode operation, verifying the cycle-pricing logic, and troubleshooting coin-drop-to-card-reader handoff during the transition period when some machines run dual-mode. The card-system vendor handles their own hardware installation and payment-processor integration; we coordinate with the vendor on timing so the laundromat isn't down longer than necessary." },
  { q: "Do you handle Dexter OPL at LA hotels and institutions?", a: "Yes. Dexter OPL installations at LA hotels, medical facilities, and institutional kitchens concentrate in a handful of operator clusters rather than across the full LA hospitality market — some hotel chains and property-management companies spec Dexter OPL consistently, while others run Speed Queen or Continental Girbau. Typical Dexter OPL service: front-load door gaskets on high-cycle O-Series units; drain pump replacements after pocket-check neglect; inverter drive diagnostics after LA brownout events; programmable controller firmware questions when OPL cycles don't match the property's linen-processing spec; and occasional belt + bearing service on high-cycle-count units. Same-day dispatch on OPL down calls given the linen-shortage cascade problem at any hotel or hospital inside 12 hours." }
