  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Dexter — Iowa, ESOP, and 1894 heritage</h2>
    <p>Dexter Laundry Inc. is a commercial laundry equipment manufacturer headquartered in Fairfield, Iowa. Dexter has been 100% employee-owned through an ESOP since 2004 — which puts Dexter 14 years ahead of Alliance Laundry Systems (Speed Queen's parent) on the employee-ownership transition. Dexter's 1894 founding makes it among the oldest continuously operating US commercial laundry makers, alongside Huebsch (1887) and Speed Queen (1908). In operational terms, Dexter's employee-ownership shows up in the product: engineering roadmap is set by employee-owners rather than subordinated to a private-equity return horizon or a conglomerate's portfolio-integration strategy.</p>
    <p>Parts and service infrastructure: Dexter runs its own direct + authorized distributor network out of Fairfield, with regional distribution into the LA market. Parts lead times run 1-3 days on common service items through the authorized channel; common replacement parts (door gaskets, door switches, water-inlet valves, drain pumps, drive belts, pulley assemblies) are stocked on our service trucks for single-visit resolution where model compatibility matches. Dexter doesn't share a parts catalog with Alliance, Ali Group, or ITW siblings the way brands inside multi-brand conglomerates sometimes do — Dexter parts are Dexter-specific.</p>
  </div></section>

